# Pull request template (required)

When opening or updating a PR for this repository:

1. Copy the structure from `.github/pull_request_template.md`.
2. Fill every section: What and Why, How, Testing (with checkboxes), Performance, Security, Migrations / Ops, Docs, Definition of Done.
3. Prefer `gh pr create --body-file` or `gh pr edit --body-file` with a file under `ibex-harness-workspace/pr-bodies/`.
4. Do not use one-line PR bodies.
5. Never store PR body drafts in the git repository.
6. No agent attribution in PR descriptions.
7. Run local tests per `testing-verification.mdc` before push.

See `docs/DEVELOPMENT_GUIDE.md` §7.2 and `CONTRIBUTING.md`.
